DISCLAIMER (SUMMARY)

This Software is an independent, unofficial tool. It is not affiliated with,
endorsed by, sponsored by, or in any way connected to the Driver and Vehicle
Standards Agency (DVSA), the UK Government, gov.uk, the DVLA, or any test
centre, instructor, or instructor-association.

The Software operates only on the DVSA "Change your test" management flow
(/manage* and /login* URLs). It is for users who already hold a confirmed
DVSA practical driving test booking and want to find an earlier cancellation
slot at the same test centre to reschedule to. It does NOT book new tests,
skip the DVSA application or payment flow, or operate on any other DVSA URL.

The Software automates actions you would otherwise take manually on this
management flow using your own login. You are responsible for ensuring your
use of the Software complies with the DVSA's terms and conditions, your
local laws, and any restrictions on test rebooking that may apply to your
account. You are responsible for verifying every booking detail before
committing it.

The Software is provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without warranty of any
kind, express or implied. To the maximum extent permitted by law, the author
disclaims all liability for any direct, indirect, incidental, special,
consequential, exemplary, or punitive damages arising from your use of, or
inability to use, the Software, including but not limited to lost test
slots, account suspensions, incorrect bookings, missed notifications, and
costs of substitute services.

By installing, copying, modifying, or using the Software you accept these
terms in full. If you do not accept them, do not install or use the Software.

The full, binding disclaimer, including assumption of risk, indemnification,
governing law (England and Wales), and the auto-book-specific waiver,is in
DISCLAIMER.md in this repository. The summary above does not replace it.
